From: nvidia-driver-injector <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: 2026-05-12
Subject: [PATCH 0007/0007] tb-egpu: version metadata + Kconfig wiring (cluster P7)

The final cluster of the P1-P6 refactor. Consolidates legacy 0005
(version-string mark) and 0025 (Kbuild reads version.mk) into one
metadata patch, and lands the Kconfig wiring per inventory Section 4
that was deferred out of P6.

Three things:

(1) NVIDIA_VERSION bump to 595.71.05-aorus.13.

    Continues the production version sequence (aorus.12 was the last
    legacy production build). The internal naming convention is
    tb_egpu_*, but the external user-visible version string keeps the
    aorus.N family so it slots into existing operational tooling
    (modinfo, container image tags) without disruption.

(2) Kbuild reads NVIDIA_VERSION from version.mk (legacy 0025 mechanism).

    Eliminates Kbuild/version.mk drift. Prior to legacy 0025, the
    -DNV_VERSION_STRING literal was hardcoded in kernel-open/Kbuild
    AND set in version.mk; subsequent patches bumped only version.mk
    and the strings drifted (Kbuild left at aorus.5 while version.mk
    reached aorus.10). Fix: have Kbuild include ../version.mk and
    use $(NVIDIA_VERSION) in the macro. Single source of truth;
    future bumps only need version.mk.

    kbuild's .cmd hashing detects the expanded -D value changing and
    rebuilds nv.o accordingly, so a bare `make modules` after a
    NVIDIA_VERSION bump produces the correct modinfo without
    `make clean`.

    Candidate for upstream as a standalone cleanup PR if NVIDIA is
    willing.

(3) Kconfig wiring (per inventory Section 4).

    Two toggles defined in kernel-open/Kbuild as Makefile variables
    (NVIDIA's kernel-open uses Makefile conditionals, not in-tree
    Kconfig integration):

      CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU       ?= y   (master gate)
      CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG  ?= n   (diagnostic telemetry gate)

    CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU is reserved/documentation-only for now. Full
    opt-out at this gate would require wrapping the eGPU additions
    across P1-P5 in #ifdef CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU — multiple hundreds of
    additional gating wraps across nv-pci.c, nv.c, the err_handlers
    struct, the include lines, etc. Out of scope for the refactor;
    flagged as a future tightening. The build is effectively
    "always y" today, with the symbol defined for future use.

    CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG is the real toggle. Default n. When n:
      - kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.c is excluded from
        NVIDIA_SOURCES (ifeq in nvidia-sources.Kbuild)
      - nv-tb-egpu-diag.h provides an inline no-op stub
        (static inline void tb_egpu_diag_dump(...) { (void)nvl;
        (void)site; }) so the 6 lifecycle call sites in nv.c +
        nv-pci.c compile to nothing
      - production binary loses ~10% per inventory Section 4

    When y: real diag function compiled in, call sites emit real
    [DIAG] / [DIAG-AER] / [DIAG-AER2] lines per cluster P6.

    Override at build time:
      make CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG=y modules

What's deliberately NOT in this patch:

- No CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU=n implementation (see above; out of scope).
- No DIAG-only sysfs gating for the qwd `last_aer_summary` /
  `last_pmc_boot_0` / `last_detection_jiffies` files that the
  inventory's Section 4 table marks DIAG-only. The current P3
  surface exposes all five qwd sysfs files unconditionally; moving
  three of them under CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG=n stub would require
  reaching back into P3 to wrap their sysfs_create_group attrs
  array conditionally. That's a real win (less attack surface on
  production), but a follow-up patch, not P7. Flagged here.
- No Kconfig file under kernel-open/. NVIDIA's kernel-open doesn't
  participate in the kernel's Kconfig system (it's an out-of-tree
  module that uses make variables, not menuconfig). The inventory
  Section 4 noted this and proposed the Makefile fallback we're
  using.

Files touched:
  version.mk                                +1/-1  (NVIDIA_VERSION bump)
  kernel-open/Kbuild                        +39/-1 (version.mk include +
                                                    Kconfig toggles)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.h      +17    (inline no-op stub
                                                    for DIAG=n)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nvidia-sources.Kbuild  +5     (conditional diag.c
                                                    source line)

Validation: git apply --check vs vanilla 595.71.05 with all 6 prior
patches stacked OK; container build (refactor-rc1) OK with
CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG default n; container build also OK with
explicit CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG=y override.

This completes Phase 2 of the P1-P6 refactor. Phase 3 (stack
validation via uninstall/reinstall cycle on production hardware)
is the next session.

---
 kernel-open/Kbuild                       | 39 +++++++++++++++++++++++-
 kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.h     | 17 +++++++++++
 kernel-open/nvidia/nvidia-sources.Kbuild |  5 +++
 version.mk                               |  2 +-
 4 files changed, 61 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel-open/Kbuild b/kernel-open/Kbuild
index 089c77d..b8b1bf6 100644
--- a/kernel-open/Kbuild
+++ b/kernel-open/Kbuild
@@ -79,7 +79,44 @@ ccflags-y += -I$(src)/common/inc
 ccflags-y += -I$(src)
 ccflags-y += -Wall $(DEFINES) $(INCLUDES) -Wno-cast-qual -Wno-format-extra-args
 ccflags-y += -D__KERNEL__ -DMODULE -DNVRM
-ccflags-y += -DNV_VERSION_STRING=\"595.71.05\"
+
+# tb-egpu (cluster P7): read NVIDIA_VERSION from the repo-root version.mk
+# so a bump there propagates to MODULE_VERSION() automatically and the
+# Kbuild value can never drift from the version.mk value. Single source
+# of truth. kbuild's .cmd hashing detects the expanded -D value changing
+# and rebuilds nv.o accordingly, so `make modules` after a version.mk
+# bump produces the correct modinfo without `make clean`.
+#
+# Candidate for upstream as a standalone cleanup if NVIDIA is willing.
+include $(src)/../version.mk
+ccflags-y += -DNV_VERSION_STRING=\"$(NVIDIA_VERSION)\"
+
+# tb-egpu (cluster P7): Kconfig-style toggles.
+#
+# CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU      master gate. Default y. Currently reserved as
+#                        a documentation-only symbol — gating P1-P5 out
+#                        would require wrapping all eGPU additions
+#                        across 6 clusters in #ifdef, out of scope for
+#                        the refactor. Build is "always y" today.
+# CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG diagnostic telemetry gate. Default n. When y,
+#                        the always-on diag content from cluster P6
+#                        compiles in (nv-tb-egpu-diag.c is included in
+#                        NVIDIA_SOURCES, and the call sites in nv.c +
+#                        nv-pci.c emit real DIAG dumps). When n, the
+#                        diag.c TU is excluded and the header provides
+#                        an inline no-op stub so call sites compile to
+#                        nothing — ~10% binary size reduction on the
+#                        production build per inventory Section 4.
+#
+# Override at build time:    make CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG=y modules
+CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU       ?= y
+CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG  ?= n
+ifeq ($(CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU),y)
+ccflags-y += -DCONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU
+endif
+ifeq ($(CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG),y)
+ccflags-y += -DCONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG
+endif
 
 # Include and link Tegra out-of-tree modules.
 ifneq ($(wildcard /usr/src/nvidia/nvidia-public),)
diff --git a/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.h b/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.h
index b47a611..6f2fc35 100644
--- a/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.h
+++ b/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.h
@@ -47,6 +47,23 @@
 struct nv_linux_state_s;
 typedef struct nv_linux_state_s nv_linux_state_t;
 
+/*
+ * Conditional gate (cluster P7). When CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG is defined
+ * by kernel-open/Kbuild, tb_egpu_diag_dump is the real function from
+ * nv-tb-egpu-diag.c. When not defined, this header provides an inline
+ * no-op stub so the 6 lifecycle call sites in nv.c / nv-pci.c compile
+ * to nothing — ~10% binary size win on production builds per inventory
+ * Section 4. Argument names are kept so the inline body can `(void)` them
+ * and avoid unused-variable warnings at the caller.
+ */
+#ifdef CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG
 void tb_egpu_diag_dump(nv_linux_state_t *nvl, const char *site);
+#else
+static inline void tb_egpu_diag_dump(nv_linux_state_t *nvl, const char *site)
+{
+    (void)nvl;
+    (void)site;
+}
+#endif
 
 #endif /* _NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG_H_ */
diff --git a/kernel-open/nvidia/nvidia-sources.Kbuild b/kernel-open/nvidia/nvidia-sources.Kbuild
index 03d4c1e..a449752 100644
--- a/kernel-open/nvidia/nvidia-sources.Kbuild
+++ b/kernel-open/nvidia/nvidia-sources.Kbuild
@@ -14,7 +14,12 @@ NVIDIA_SOURCES += nvidia/nv-pci.c
 NVIDIA_SOURCES += nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-aer.c
 NVIDIA_SOURCES += nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-qwd.c
 NVIDIA_SOURCES += nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-recover.c
+# tb-egpu (cluster P7): diag TU is gated by CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG
+# (default n in kernel-open/Kbuild). When n, the header provides an
+# inline no-op stub so call sites compile to nothing.
+ifeq ($(CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG),y)
 NVIDIA_SOURCES += nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.c
+endif
 NVIDIA_SOURCES += nvidia/nv-dmabuf.c
 NVIDIA_SOURCES += nvidia/nv-nano-timer.c
 NVIDIA_SOURCES += nvidia/nv-acpi.c
diff --git a/version.mk b/version.mk
index ea15e65..698cab0 100644
--- a/version.mk
+++ b/version.mk
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
-NVIDIA_VERSION = 595.71.05
+NVIDIA_VERSION = 595.71.05-aorus.13
 NVIDIA_NVID_VERSION = 595.71.05
 NVIDIA_NVID_EXTRA = 
 
